news.title: HomeLane acquires DesignCafe, raises Rs 225 crore
news.para: After the acquisition, HomeLane raised Rs 225 crore from new investors, including Sunil Kant Munjal’s Hero Enterprise and Claypond Capital, the family office of Manipal Group’s Ranjan Pai, with participation from existing investors such as WestBridge Capital and others.

news.title: OECD calls for higher property taxes to fight debt
news.para: In its economic oulook report titled "Turning the Corner", the Paris-based organisation said global gross domestic product would expand by 3.2 percent, compared to 3.1 percent in its previous forecast.

news.title: US FTC fines Invitation Homes $48 million over hidden fees
news.para: The company charged tens of millions of dollars' worth of undisclosed fees between 2021 and 2023, including charges for air filter delivery, smart home technology, and "utility management," the FTC said.

news.title: Flexible office space operators secure $820 million in PE funding since 2017: Report
news.para: "From 2017 to 2018, investments grew steadily from USD 25 million to USD 49 million, rising sharply to USD 113 million in 2019, driven by investors like CLSA Capital and Peak XV Partners."

news.title: Mt K Kapital raises over Rs 500 crore to invest in realty projects in Mumbai
news.para: Over Rs 300 crore has already been committed towards five projects in the Mumbai region by Keystone Realtors (Rustomjee Group).

news.title: Flent raises Rs 6.5 crore in pre-seed funding
news.para: The funding round also saw participation from US-based 2 AM Ventures, Pareto Holdings, and a group of angel investors, including Sanchan S Saxena (Ex-GM, Airbnb), Aneesh Reddy (Founder, Capillary Technologies), Arjun Vaidya (Founder, Dr. Vaidya’s), and Abhilash N (Co-founder, Ivy Homes).

news.title: Maha Metro set to open three new metro stations from September 26
news.para: The three stations on the stretch are Kasba Peth, Mandai and Swargate. "We will keep all machinery ready to operate the trains for commuters on Thursday. Having said that, we are yet to receive confirmation on this front from the authorities," a Maha Metro official said on Tuesday.

news.title: Hudco raises $448 million loan from three banks of Japan
news.para: Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group (MUFG), Sumitomo Mitsui Banking Corp (SMBC) and Mizuho Bank, three of the largest banking groups in Japan by assets, have come together to finance a rare loan for Hudco, people familiar with the development said.

news.title: Maharashtra CM clears PMRDA budget of Rs 3,838 crore
news.para: While chairing the annual PMRDA budget meeting in Mumbai, the CM emphasized that affordable housing schemes in the Pune Metropolitan Region (PMR) need to be properly planned with the help of experts, and adequate open spaces must be incorporated.

news.title: Britain's Rightmove rejects $8.1 billion takeover proposal from REA Group
news.para: "The board considered the increased proposal ... and concluded that the increased proposal continues to be unattractive and materially undervalues the company and its future prospects," Rightmove said in a statement.

news.title: Delhi: All 10 flats in Dwarka issued for e-auction by DDA sold out on September 24
news.para: The officials stated that on the first day of the e auction of the DDA Dwarka flats, all 10 flats put under bidding were sold out.

news.title: Country Garden Services to sell stake in Zhuhai Wanda for $446 million
news.para: The sale allows the company to streamline its investments, recover capital, and refocus on its core business operations as part of its planned exit strategy, it said.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: TNUHDB to demolish weak building and build new one in Trichy
news.para: ​​This comes in the wake of people complaining to Trichy corporation about the perilous state of the building. Mayor Mu Anbalagan on Tuesday inspected the property and suggested to TNUHDB officials to prepare an estimate for the new building.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body razes 27 structures in blue floodline zone on September 24
news.para: A senior Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) official confirmed to TOI that at least 27 constructions were demolished on the first day of the drive on Tuesday, as they were found inside the blue line zones of the Pavana, Mula and Indrayani rivers.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC upholds PCB order to impose 14 crore fine on brick kilns in Haridwar
news.para: The brick kiln owners sought a stay on the PCB orders which had levied fines amounting to Rs 14 crore for environmental violations and had ordered the closure of their operations due to non-payment.

news.title: Telangana government to give 2-BHKs for all affected in Musi riverfront project
news.para: "The deserving poor families should not be left on the streets. They should be allotted a double bedroom house or given some other rehabilitation alternative. Collect the details of all the eligible poor living in the Musi FTL and buffer zone, and other ponds and canals within the ORR. Make sure that all the deserving poor are rehabilitated.

news.title: Noida authority to allot plots for six new hotels in city
news.para: The six hotel plots collectively span 42,790 sqm, with a total reserve price of Rs 781.48 crores. The allotment process will be conducted through an e-auction, with a pre-bid meeting scheduled for Oct 10 to address potential bidders' queries.

news.title: DTCP takes action against 11 illegal buildings in Gurugram's Palam Vihar
news.para: Each 500 sq yd plot, originally meant to have a single housing unit per floor, has as many as 16 unauthorised flats. District town planner (enforcement) Manish Yadav has written to the MCG commissioner, GMDA executive engineer and DHBVN requesting the disconnections.

news.title: NBCC moves SC to complete stalled projects of Supertech
news.para: ​These 17 projects were launched in the National Capital Region, Dehradun and Bengaluru but completion of the residential units was hit due to financial crisis faced by the realty major which led to insolvency proceedings since 2021.

news.title: SC orders Ricardo Construction to compensate 31 buyers for delay in possession
news.para: In this case, NCDRC had foreclosed right of the real estate company to file a response after it did not adhere to the timeline fixed under the law. As the company would not be able to put on record its stand and counter homebuyers allegation before the commission which would affect its case, the builder approached SC to allow it to file response.
